## Section 5 — Output Format

When an agent processes a source document using these guidelines, the output should be a structured chunking plan in the following format. This is what gets reviewed before anything is embedded or inserted into Supabase.

```
CHUNKING PLAN: [source_doc_identifier]
SOURCE FILE: [filename]
PROCESSED BY: [agent identifier or timestamp]

================================================
BEHAVIORAL CONTENT FLAGGED (not chunked):
================================================
- [Section name or line range]: [Brief description of what this content instructs]
- [Section name or line range]: [Brief description]

================================================
CHUNKS:
================================================

CHUNK 1
  chunk_id:     [source_short]_[label]
  stage:        [value]
  domain:       [value]
  content_type: [value]
  kpi_family:   [value or NONE]
  source_doc:   [identifier]
  notes:        [any flags, uncertainties, or edge case notes]
  content:      [The actual text of this chunk — exact copy from source, no paraphrasing]

CHUNK 2
  [same structure]

...

================================================
TAXONOMY EXTENSIONS PROPOSED:
================================================
- [field]: [proposed new value] — [definition and rationale]

================================================
REVIEW FLAGS:
================================================
- [Any chunking decisions that need human verification]
```

Each chunk's `content` field should be the verbatim text from the source document. No summarization, no paraphrasing. The chunk is exactly what will be embedded and stored.

